description: From Maori rātā or cognate Tahitian rātā (tree of genus Metrosideros). Compare Tahitian puarātā (Metrosideros collina).

entries.meaning: (usually countable) Any of various New Zealand plants of the genus Metrosideros
(usually uncountable) The hard dark red wood of such trees.

description: Compare Sinhalese රට ගොරකා (raṭa gorakā, “Garcinia xanthochymus”), Marathi रातंबी (rātambī, “Garcinia indica”).

entries.meaning: The yellow mangosteen, Garcinia dulcis, a tree native to Indonesia, the Philippines, and India.
examples: Synonyms: mundu, maphuut, Claudie mangosteen, gourka, eggtree
